Well, the common American
nigger of course.

76
00:07:51,312 --> 00:07:52,347
Damn it, I've heard enough...

77
00:07:52,580 --> 00:07:53,807
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

78
00:08:00,604 --> 00:08:03,189
All right.

79
00:08:10,614 --> 00:08:13,575
Never thought I'd see you again.

80
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:15,401
You kill him?

81
00:08:17,404 --> 00:08:19,914
Where you going?

82
00:08:20,039 --> 00:08:23,545
Sooner or later,
you gotta give us some orders, boss man.

83
00:08:24,777 --> 00:08:27,254
The demise of head
surveyor Robert Bell

84
00:08:27,379 --> 00:08:29,724
and party, a great loss to railroad.

85
00:08:29,849 --> 00:08:31,125
Stop.

86
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:34,562
Bell's work must continue.
Stop.

87
00:08:34,687 --> 00:08:37,831
Send funds for new surveyors at once.

88
00:08:37,956 --> 00:08:39,269
Stop.

89
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,359
What news?

90
00:08:46,525 --> 00:08:52,445
Payroll is late... work
disorganized and slow.

91
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:56,014
This new foreman of yours
just up and leave yesterday.

92
00:08:56,139 --> 00:08:57,662
Nobody seen him since.

93
00:08:57,828 --> 00:09:00,748
He rode out to rendez-vous
with the tree cutting party.

94
00:09:00,914 --> 00:09:05,795
He informed me yesterday
at our morning briefing.

95
00:09:05,961 --> 00:09:08,025
There's something about this man.

96
00:09:08,150 --> 00:09:10,008
He's up to something.

97
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:12,430
He crossed paths with Mrs. Bell.

98
00:09:12,555 --> 00:09:13,665
Bohannon?

99
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:15,054
He brought her in.

100
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:16,264
Did she have the maps?

101
00:09:16,492 --> 00:09:17,568
Shh.

102
00:09:17,693 --> 00:09:19,267
She's right next door.

103
00:09:21,863 --> 00:09:25,442
No, she didn't have them.

104
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:29,152
How will you reach the
Pacific without them?

105
00:09:29,318 --> 00:09:30,653
You let me worry about that.

106
00:09:32,407 --> 00:09:36,743
Oh, there's a supply train
arriving tomorrow morning

107
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:39,454
with a shipment of black powder.

108
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:44,459
My men will meet the train
and guard it all morning.

109
00:09:49,122 --> 00:09:52,425
New telegram to my damn stock broker.

110
00:09:52,592 --> 00:10:00,241
Invest $147,000 in R&R
railroad stock as discussed.

111
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:01,851
Stop.

112
00:10:12,144 --> 00:10:13,821
Ahem.

113
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,114
Mrs. Bell?

114
00:10:20,885 --> 00:10:22,830
Are you all right in there?

115
00:10:24,455 --> 00:10:27,834
Yes, thank you, Mr. Durant.

116
00:10:27,959 --> 00:10:31,137
I, uh, ahem, I brought out my...

117
00:10:31,262 --> 00:10:34,841
Personal Chef from Delmonico's
in New York City.

118
00:10:34,966 --> 00:10:39,778
I wondered if you would like to
join me for dinner this evening?

119
00:10:39,903 --> 00:10:42,539
Yes, that would be wonderful.

120
00:10:47,978 --> 00:10:50,483
Is there anything else
I can get for you?

121
00:10:54,184 --> 00:10:59,064
Actually, has the reward
been given to anyone?

122
00:10:59,189 --> 00:11:01,995
Uh, I believe it
belongs to Mr. Bohannon.

123
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:03,868
I don't think he's claimed it.

124
00:11:03,993 --> 00:11:05,456
Would you like me
to see that he gets it?

125
00:11:05,622 --> 00:11:07,372
No.

126
00:11:07,497 --> 00:11:10,378
There's someone else who deserves it.

127
00:11:42,795 --> 00:11:44,639
Stay off my corner, sweetheart,

128
00:11:44,764 --> 00:11:47,333
unless she wants her
own crib, right, ladies?

129
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:51,085
Leave her alone.

130
00:11:51,251 --> 00:11:52,481
What do you say, blondie?

131
00:11:52,606 --> 00:11:54,516
Them Injuns teach you anything?

132
00:11:54,641 --> 00:11:56,518
Leave her alone!

133
00:11:56,643 --> 00:11:58,551
Hey, I'm sorry, ma'am.

134
00:11:58,717 --> 00:12:01,471
These dirty whores don't know
a lady when they see one.

135
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:09,029
Where there is hatred,
let me show love.

136
00:12:09,154 --> 00:12:12,333
Where there is injury, pardon.

137
00:12:12,458 --> 00:12:15,276
Where there is doubt, faith.

138
00:12:15,442 --> 00:12:17,203
Amen.

139
00:12:17,328 --> 00:12:19,229
Joseph?

140
00:12:20,465 --> 00:12:22,799
Mrs. Bell?

141
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:27,914
You look like you're
feeling much better.

142
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,458
It's amazing what
a little soap and water can do.

143
00:12:32,008 --> 00:12:34,003
I didn't mean to leave that night.

144
00:12:34,169 --> 00:12:35,454
But that man...

145
00:12:35,579 --> 00:12:37,340
There's no need to explain.

146
00:12:38,582 --> 00:12:40,176
You've cut your hair.

147
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:41,793
Yes, ma'am.

148
00:12:41,918 --> 00:12:43,012
Did you come to pray?

149
00:12:43,178 --> 00:12:46,631
No, um... I came to give you this.

150
00:12:46,756 --> 00:12:49,099
It's the reward money.
No, please, take it.

151
00:12:49,224 --> 00:12:50,645
I can't.

152
00:12:50,811 --> 00:12:53,078
There'll be no trouble,
nobody knows it was you.

153
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:55,339
No, that's not it.

154
00:12:55,464 --> 00:12:57,860
I'm not a bounty hunter.

155
00:12:58,026 --> 00:12:59,743
It's my duty to help.

156
00:12:59,868 --> 00:13:02,979
Joseph, that money will
buy a lot of bibles.

157
00:13:03,104 --> 00:13:05,868
Mrs. Bell, Reverend Cole.

158
00:13:06,034 --> 00:13:07,941
Reverend.

159
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:10,094
Your donations are always welcome.

160
00:13:11,039 --> 00:13:12,708
Please.

161
00:13:12,874 --> 00:13:14,794
Thank you.

162
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,838
So, this is the fair-haired
maiden of the West?

163
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:18,589
I beg your pardon?

164
00:13:28,181 --> 00:13:31,139
"Robert Bell fought valiantly to save

165
00:13:31,264 --> 00:13:32,478
the virtue of his beautiful wife,

166
00:13:32,644 --> 00:13:36,702
killing a savage
with his final breath.

167
00:13:38,904 --> 00:13:40,653
Is that not how it happened?

168
00:13:40,819 --> 00:13:43,017
Yes.

169
00:13:43,142 --> 00:13:47,118
My husband... saved my life.

170
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:50,037
Well... what about
the rest of it? Um...

171
00:13:51,496 --> 00:13:52,957
Outnumbered 10 to one?

172
00:13:53,123 --> 00:13:54,834
Sullied by the savages?

173
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,544
I didn't write it.

174
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:58,045
But this is true?

175
00:13:58,211 --> 00:13:59,422
Of course not.

176
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:01,841
Well, Indians will die
as a result of this.

177
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:03,704
The Indians attacked us.

178
00:14:03,829 --> 00:14:06,471
If they die, they will
be to blame, not me.

179
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:07,638
Maybe you've heard of
the Sand Creek massacre?

180
00:14:07,804 --> 00:14:09,265
I didn't come here to speak of this.

181
00:14:09,431 --> 00:14:11,745
You know, the Cheyenne were
flying the American flag

182
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:13,579
over their camp and it
didn't stop the U.S. Calvary

183
00:14:13,704 --> 00:14:16,314
from killing 100 innocent
women and children.

184
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,383
That was a terrible
thing that happened.

185
00:14:17,508 --> 00:14:18,900
I wasn't a part of it.

186
00:14:19,066 --> 00:14:20,220
Please, I'm just saying,

187
00:14:20,345 --> 00:14:21,611
try to see the bigger picture.

188
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:23,822
My husband was slaughtered
right in front of me.

189
00:14:23,947 --> 00:14:28,075
It's a little difficult
to see the bigger picture.

190
00:14:28,241 --> 00:14:29,886
Good day.

191
00:14:59,281 --> 00:15:01,115
Hey.

192
00:15:02,784 --> 00:15:04,594
Hey, hey.

193
00:15:04,719 --> 00:15:08,155
That son of a bitch
got away because of you.

194
00:15:09,624 --> 00:15:11,233
Because of me?
How you figure that?

195
00:15:11,358 --> 00:15:14,121
You killed Johnson before
he could give me Harper's name.

196
00:15:16,206 --> 00:15:17,372
Oh.

197
00:15:17,497 --> 00:15:21,045
Well, I... I killed Johnson
before he killed you.

198
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:22,611
Now...

199
00:15:22,736 --> 00:15:24,423
But I would have got
a name out of him.

200
00:15:24,589 --> 00:15:25,967
He would have blowed your brains out.

201
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,182
And then I could have killed Harper

202
00:15:27,307 --> 00:15:28,761
before he had a chance to run.

203
00:15:28,927 --> 00:15:31,277
You're either drunk or crazy or both.

204
00:15:35,248 --> 00:15:37,645
You have any idea
what they took from me?

205
00:15:39,585 --> 00:15:43,025
They ain't took nothin' from you
that ain't been took from me.

206
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:52,129
Fly away home, just a nickel a show.

207
00:15:53,618 --> 00:15:56,076
Feel the mist against your cheeks.

208
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,749
Give it a rest, Mick.

209
00:15:58,915 --> 00:16:04,328
They're sick and bloody tired
of the mighty Shannon

210
00:16:04,453 --> 00:16:09,051
and the blarney stone...
The bloody Irish bog.

211
00:16:09,217 --> 00:16:11,801
Well, then we need new slides.

212
00:16:11,926 --> 00:16:13,806
New slides cost money.

213
00:16:13,972 --> 00:16:15,600
You've got some copper
squirreled away, brother,

214
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:16,767
now's the time to tell me.

215
00:16:16,933 --> 00:16:18,686
Maybe we should relocate.

216
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:21,230
The rent is low down by
the slaughterhouse, right?

217
00:16:21,396 --> 00:16:22,478
The rent was low
in Wicklow, too, Mick.

218
00:16:24,983 --> 00:16:26,705
We're done with that shit.

219
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:30,281
It was a high rent dream
that brought us out here.

220
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:34,535
I'm not going to let that big
Swedish bastard kill our dream.

221
00:16:34,701 --> 00:16:36,324
Am I right?

222
00:16:36,449 --> 00:16:38,873
Mick?

223
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:41,167
Hold on now.

224
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:43,753
I just had a grand idea.

225
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:45,671
Oh, no.

226
00:16:45,837 --> 00:16:47,424
It's a business idea.

227
00:16:48,894 --> 00:16:51,204
Ideas ain't your strong suit, Mick.

228
00:16:51,329 --> 00:16:52,720
Ah, ha ha.

229
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:54,040
This one's golden.

230
00:16:54,165 --> 00:16:55,640
I'll prove it to ya.

231
00:16:57,641 --> 00:17:02,021
I've taken the liberty of
telegraphing your family in England.

232
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:04,950
I just wanted them
to know you were well.

233
00:17:05,075 --> 00:17:06,853
Thank you, Mr. Durant.

234
00:17:06,978 --> 00:17:10,112
I'm afraid you'll grow
weary of my gratitude.

235
00:17:10,278 --> 00:17:13,783
I don't know what news of
the attack may have reached them.

236
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:17,953
I didn't want your father
worrying needlessly.

237
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:20,365
I'm sure my father was happy to hear

238
00:17:20,490 --> 00:17:23,167
he was right...

239
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,960
About me coming to America.

240
00:17:25,126 --> 00:17:26,796
He was against it, no doubt?

241
00:17:26,962 --> 00:17:30,307
My father had every aspect
of my life planned out,

242
00:17:30,432 --> 00:17:32,051
including whom I should marry.

243
00:17:34,052 --> 00:17:36,337
Robert interrupted those plans.

244
00:17:40,375 --> 00:17:42,228
I saw him give a lecture

245
00:17:42,394 --> 00:17:45,481
at the British Museum
of Natural History.

246
00:17:45,647 --> 00:17:48,782
He spoke of the American West.

247
00:17:54,022 --> 00:17:57,066
I fell in love...

248
00:17:57,191 --> 00:18:00,746
With him and with this land.

249
00:18:00,912 --> 00:18:04,706
I, too, came under Robert's spell.

250
00:18:04,831 --> 00:18:09,645
His dream of a transcontinental
railroad became my own.

251
00:18:09,770 --> 00:18:13,906
Then it's a shame you two had
such a terrible falling out.

252
00:18:14,175 --> 00:18:18,180
Well, Robert and I didn't
see eye to eye on everything.

253
00:18:18,346 --> 00:18:22,518
Such as how to squeeze every
last dollar out of the railroad.

254
00:18:25,217 --> 00:18:30,317
Mrs. Bell, your husband
was a starry-eyed dreamer.

255
00:18:30,483 --> 00:18:32,695
I am a realist.

256
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:35,735
Without me, his dream would
have remained just that.

257
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:38,325
Thank you for your hospitality,
Mr. Durant.

258
00:18:39,798 --> 00:18:41,632
Mrs. Bell, please, I'm sorry.

259
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:44,373
I didn't mean to impugn Robert.

260
00:18:44,539 --> 00:18:48,046
Yes, he needed me,
but I needed him also.

261
00:18:48,171 --> 00:18:52,089
Our marriage wasn't
perfect, but it worked.

262
00:18:54,257 --> 00:18:57,322
Mrs. Bell, there's nowhere
for you to go out there.

263
00:18:57,447 --> 00:19:00,765
Please... accept my apology.

264
00:19:02,252 --> 00:19:05,253
Do me the honor
of remaining my guest.

265
00:19:53,499 --> 00:19:54,944
Why you following me?

